+# Node HTTP and HTTPS Servers for Testing
+
+This document describes the usage of Node-based HTTP and HTTPS servers for networking tests in Mozilla.
+
+## head_servers.sys.mjs
+
+The previous `head_servers.js` has been converted into an ES module named `head_servers.sys.mjs` to allow reuse across all xpcshell tests.
+
+### Importing the module
+
+js
+import { NodeHTTPServers } from "resource://testing-common/head_servers.sys.mjs";
+
+const servers = new NodeHTTPServers();
+const httpServer = await servers.startHTTP();
+const httpsServer = await servers.startHTTPS();
+// Use servers in your tests...
+
+
+### HTTPS Server and Certificate Import
+
+The HTTPS server automatically imports the server certificate into the test environment's certificate database using `certutil`, if available.
+
+This ensures that HTTPS connections in tests do not fail due to untrusted certificates.
+
+If the import fails or `certutil` is not found, a warning is logged, but the test does not fail.
+
+### Certificate Files
+
+The server key and certificate files are located in the `certs` directory alongside `head_servers.sys.mjs`.
+
+Tests should ensure these files are present for HTTPS server usage.
+
